And you ain't earned mine yet!

40:58.873 --> 41:01.333
You gotta earn mine before
you get back on the damn field.

41:02.668 --> 41:05.629
You think you better than you damn are
and you ain't!

41:06.547 --> 41:09.800
We may be a team that just competes
with an 0-3 team,

41:10.593 --> 41:12.303
but that ain't what your ass
came here for.

41:13.304 --> 41:16.432
Some of you were brought here
because we thought you were players.

41:17.433 --> 41:19.560
I think I may be wrong.

41:19.643 --> 41:24.732
I fucked up recruiting
'cause I let your asses come in here.

41:24.815 --> 41:26.108
Some of ya.

41:26.192 --> 41:27.943
I fucked up on recruiting.

41:28.027 --> 41:31.489
Now, you either decide to play
or your ass won't be around here anymore.

41:31.572 --> 41:32.698
Be the damn leader.

41:33.532 --> 41:36.702
Set your damn feet and throw it!
It's all a fuckin' excuse!

41:37.745 --> 41:40.372
I'm tired of seeing us
under-fuckin'-achieve.

41:40.456 --> 41:43.292
As a coaching staff and as a damn team.

41:44.543 --> 41:47.046
Now, by God, get after their ass
in the second half.

41:47.129 --> 41:50.299
We're gonna get the fuckin' ball and
we're gonna shove it up their damn nose.

41:50.382 --> 41:52.510
Now get your asses ready to play.

41:57.306 --> 41:59.850
[Wyatt] Let's go, man. Let's go.
It's good. Let's do it.

41:59.934 --> 42:03.229
Y'all look like it's the first time
y'all ever been cussed out before.

42:03.312 --> 42:06.607
[CJ] Coach said "dominate," brother,
and we not doin' that shit, bro.

42:06.690 --> 42:08.651
Our wideouts are way better
than these wideouts, bro.

42:08.734 --> 42:11.529
[stuttering] Everyday in practice we're
doing... Come on, man. Let's go, bro.

42:11.612 --> 42:14.240
-[player] Y'all right there, make a play.
-Let's dominate, bro.

42:14.323 --> 42:15.491
"Dominate" on three, bro.

42:15.574 --> 42:17.284
-One, two, three...
-[all] Dominate!

42:21.413 --> 42:23.332
You gotta expect that shit, man.
I'm telling you, man.

42:23.415 --> 42:25.376
You good, baby.
Just play.

42:28.879 --> 42:30.339
I'm not worried about the score,

42:30.422 --> 42:33.717
I'm not worried about anything else,
other than the next drive.

42:33.801 --> 42:35.219
The next play. That's it!

42:35.302 --> 42:36.929
[players grunting]

42:38.472 --> 42:39.515
[announcer 1] <i>Trips nearside.</i>

42:39.598 --> 42:41.392
<i>EMCC wanting to go fast.</i>
<i>Here's the snap to Roberts.</i>

42:41.475 --> 42:42.810
<i>Roberts gonna leave it</i>
<i>on the ground with Law.</i>

42:42.893 --> 42:44.770
<i>Law coming around nearside.</i>
<i>He's gonna be hit...</i>

42:44.853 --> 42:46.564
<i>uh, by a couple of guys</i>
<i>who he pinballs off of.</i>

42:46.647 --> 42:48.941
<i>He stays down the nearside line,</i>
<i>he may score.</i>

42:49.024 --> 42:53.153
<i>He's inside the 30, 20, 15,</i>
<i>ten, five, touchdown! DJ Law!</i>

42:53.237 --> 42:55.114
<i>Unbelievable!</i>

42:55.197 --> 42:57.366
<i>Law got absolutely smoked.</i>

42:57.449 --> 43:00.077
[Trickett] Good fucking run, baby!

43:00.160 --> 43:02.788
That's what I'm fuckin' talking about.
Good shit, DJ!

43:02.871 --> 43:04.540
Good fuckin' run!

43:04.623 --> 43:06.875
[announcer 1] <i>Good, now that's</i>
<i>54-yards on the touchdown run</i>

43:06.959 --> 43:09.044
<i>for DJ Law and EMCC is up</i>

43:09.128 --> 43:11.380
<i>20 to 7, pending the PAT.</i>
<i>What a run, Glenn.</i>

43:11.463 --> 43:13.173
-[announcer 2] <i>What a run.</i>
-I bounced off that shit.

43:13.257 --> 43:15.593
-[indistinct chatter]
-[laughing]

43:31.483 --> 43:34.445
[Buddy] Let's go.
[player] There you go. There you go.

43:34.528 --> 43:36.196
[indistinct chatter]

43:36.280 --> 43:38.032
[announcer 1] <i>In the shotgun,</i>
<i>awaits the snap. Here it is.</i>

43:38.115 --> 43:39.283
<i>He's back to pass, has time.</i>

43:39.366 --> 43:41.869
<i>Fires it nearside</i>
<i>and it's intercepted at the 29!</i>

43:41.952 --> 43:46.540
<i>Going down the nearside line,</i>
<i>15, ten, five, touchdown, EMCC!</i>

43:46.624 --> 43:50.794
<i>CJ Reavis will make the pick-six</i>
<i>from the 29 and score.</i>

43:50.878 --> 43:53.672
<i>CJ Reavis, once he caught</i>
<i>that one at the 29,</i>

43:53.756 --> 43:56.342
<i>that was a safe touchdown call.</i>

44:17.446 --> 44:19.323
[crowd cheering]

44:19.406 --> 44:20.699
[whistle blows]

44:20.783 --> 44:22.409
[player] Let's go, bro. Let's go!

44:22.493 --> 44:24.286
1-0 again, baby. Let's go!

44:24.370 --> 44:26.330
[announcer 1] <i>A fade pattern, nearside.</i>
<i>He has Lanier...</i>

44:26.413 --> 44:28.582
[announcer 2] <i>What a catch!</i>
[announcer 1] <i>He caught it!</i>

44:28.666 --> 44:30.292
<i>Touchdown!</i>

44:30.376 --> 44:32.294
<i>Oh, my goodness!</i>
<i>Are you kidding me!</i>

44:32.378 --> 44:34.713
[announcer 2] <i>Guys, that was</i>
<i>a phenomenal catch by Lanier.</i>

44:34.797 --> 44:36.840
[announcer 1] <i>He caught that ball?</i>
[announcer 2] <i>He did.</i>

44:36.924 --> 44:39.343
<i>Down at his knees, falling back...</i>

44:39.426 --> 44:41.887
Your ass is a good football team,
you understand?

44:41.970 --> 44:43.972
-[players] Yes, sir!
-Don't make me go into the halftime

44:44.056 --> 44:45.516
and do that bullshit no more.

44:45.599 --> 44:48.435
You play from the damn word "go."
Great job, guys! Great job!

44:48.519 --> 44:50.604
That's a heck of a good job

44:50.729 --> 44:54.149
to come back and play
the way you can play! Hey!

44:54.233 --> 44:55.734
You ain't gotta be back
till Sunday at curfew.

44:55.818 --> 44:57.986
[all cheering]

45:14.211 --> 45:15.254
[TV playing]

45:15.337 --> 45:17.506
[babbling]

45:20.300 --> 45:21.760
Dreads...

45:24.596 --> 45:26.432
Re-twist...

45:26.515 --> 45:28.934
[man on TV] <i>When we come back,</i>
<i>the story of the Georgia running back</i>

45:29.017 --> 45:32.855
<i>who is so good,</i>
<i>he has a town named after him.</i>

45:32.938 --> 45:35.649
-[baby humming]
-[Ollie] All right.

45:38.277 --> 45:39.445
[groans]

45:40.487 --> 45:42.448
-Mama!
-[Takesha] Mmm?

45:42.531 --> 45:45.075
She put... She puttin' her shoes on.
We finna' go.

45:46.243 --> 45:48.412
[indistinct chatter]

45:54.543 --> 45:56.879
[Rachel] <i>When he started playing,</i>
<i>at the time, when he was pee-wee,</i>

45:56.962 --> 45:58.922
the coaches always tell him,
"If you get a sack,

45:59.006 --> 46:01.175
we'll take you out to eat pizza."

46:01.258 --> 46:02.843
Oh, my God. [laughs]

46:02.926 --> 46:06.138
He get four or five of 'em.
He wouldn't stop.

46:06.221 --> 46:08.807
And then they'd tell him again.
Next day, someone would holler,

46:08.891 --> 46:10.309
"I'll give you $10,
I'll give you some money

46:10.392 --> 46:12.227
if you do this, do that, at the game."

46:12.311 --> 46:13.979
So, he was determined to do that.

46:16.106 --> 46:18.484
[Vera] <i>When I first saw him</i>
<i>play football in high school...</i>

46:18.567 --> 46:19.610
You know, I don't know
nothin' about football,

46:19.693 --> 46:22.029
but I couldn't sit down.
He won't let me sit down.

46:23.238 --> 46:25.407
If I sat down, I was scared
I was gonna miss somethin'.

46:25.491 --> 46:28.285
When they holler his name,
I said, "Oh, my God."

46:28.368 --> 46:31.371
<i>It's good to have a child</i>
<i>going this way.</i>

46:35.501 --> 46:37.252
[Takesha] <i>He was small,</i>
<i>he was only five.</i>

46:37.336 --> 46:39.171
<i>He was five when it happened.</i>

46:40.214 --> 46:43.342
<i>So, he really probably can't tell you</i>
<i>nothing about it, but...</i>

46:44.259 --> 46:45.677
<i>Actually, we was here.</i>

46:45.761 --> 46:47.888
At the time, my mama was renting
this same trailer right now

46:47.971 --> 46:49.515
that our cousin is renting.

46:51.934 --> 46:54.186
[Rachel] <i>Been home about 10:00 that night</i>

46:54.269 --> 46:56.230
<i>somebody was knocking on my door.</i>

46:56.313 --> 46:58.899
<i>I thought it was my son coming back home.</i>

46:58.982 --> 47:01.735
But it wasn't him.
It was him.

47:01.818 --> 47:04.321
Ronald's father, looking for her.

47:05.989 --> 47:08.492
<i>He always down here botherin' her,</i>
<i>pickin' at her.</i>

47:08.575 --> 47:09.826
<i>She just called the police.</i>

47:09.910 --> 47:11.578
Kept callin' the police.
Kept calling...

47:11.662 --> 47:12.829
When he would come down here

47:12.913 --> 47:15.207
and get into it with her,
I always could hear it.

47:15.290 --> 47:17.292
You know, 'cause I was just right there.

47:17.376 --> 47:21.296
But this particular night,
it just wasn't meant for me to hear.

47:21.380 --> 47:23.090
[Takesha] <i>I could hear the argument.</i>

47:23.173 --> 47:25.634
<i>They was arguing.</i>
<i>Like, my room was the...</i>

47:25.717 --> 47:28.887
<i>first window over here</i>
<i>and his was the second.</i>

47:28.971 --> 47:31.014
You know,
I'm just listening to the argument

47:31.098 --> 47:33.058
then the next thing I hear, gunshot.

47:34.935 --> 47:38.063
When I hear the gunshots, I jump up,
I ran out, I see him running.

47:38.146 --> 47:40.774
Running straight through this path.
And went around here.

47:40.857 --> 47:42.818
And the police was chasing him.

47:42.901 --> 47:45.195
And they said... police said
by the time they make it to him,

47:45.279 --> 47:46.572
they heard a gunshot.

47:46.655 --> 47:50.784
He had shot himself under...
Shot and killed himself.

47:50.867 --> 47:52.035
Mmm-hmm.

47:53.495 --> 47:54.955
Yeah.

47:55.038 --> 47:56.915
[Takesha] <i>Yeah, he'll call me,</i>
<i>he'll talk about it.</i>

47:56.999 --> 47:59.793
<i>Because it was his mom and his dad.</i>
<i>It wasn't our dad.</i>

47:59.876 --> 48:03.130
<i>So, you know, for him to lose his mom</i>
<i>and his dad, you know what I'm sayin'?</i>

48:03.213 --> 48:06.258
<i>I can only imagine 'cause, like I said,</i>
<i>he was only five.</i>

48:06.842 --> 48:09.136
<i>Like, we were leaving the hospital</i>
<i>when our mama got killed,</i>

48:09.219 --> 48:11.054
he was like, "We leavin' mama?"

48:11.138 --> 48:13.724
He thought that she was gonna be all right
and come home.

48:13.807 --> 48:16.310
He didn't get the understanding there,
like, she's gone forever.

48:16.393 --> 48:18.395
He just thought she was gone to the back.

48:18.478 --> 48:19.771
I guess 'cause he was so young

48:19.855 --> 48:22.190
but he thought that
she was supposed to come with us

48:22.274 --> 48:25.527
but that was a night
that took a toll on all of us.

48:29.781 --> 48:31.908
<i>But like, in the beginning, like,</i>
<i>I could look at him,</i>

48:31.992 --> 48:35.329
and I could see his dad.
He looks like his dad too.

48:35.412 --> 48:36.872
And I used to just be like,

48:36.955 --> 48:39.333
"Boy, I can't stand your daddy,"
and people used to tell me, like,

48:39.416 --> 48:41.376
"Don't say that to him."
You know what I'm sayin'?

48:41.460 --> 48:43.879
They felt like, if it weren't
for Ronald's dad,

48:43.962 --> 48:45.380
they mom would be living.

48:45.464 --> 48:48.091
And I had to sit down
and go through that with them.

48:48.175 --> 48:50.218
I said Ronald didn't ask for that.

48:50.302 --> 48:51.470
<i>He's still your brother.</i>

48:51.553 --> 48:54.097
<i>You know, he got a lot</i>
<i>bottled up inside of him too.</i>

48:54.181 --> 48:57.184
<i>He feel like people don't love him,</i>
<i>nobody loves him.</i>

48:57.267 --> 49:00.312
You know, he'll say that sometime.
"Why nobody don't love me?"

49:00.395 --> 49:02.230
I said, "People..."
I said, "I love you."

49:02.314 --> 49:03.607
<i>I said, "We do love you."</i>

49:03.690 --> 49:07.277
<i>You know, they'd be</i>
<i>in this feelings, then. Mmm-hmm.</i>

49:09.821 --> 49:12.783
We couldn't do nothing.
And I know they couldn't do nothing.

49:13.700 --> 49:14.868
But...

49:16.995 --> 49:18.372
we're gonna make it.

49:19.122 --> 49:20.791
<i>But, y'all keep praying for us.</i>

49:21.750 --> 49:23.251
<i>And he'll go further.</i>

49:23.335 --> 49:26.088
<i>Let him go furthest he can go, Lord.</i>

49:26.171 --> 49:28.507
<i>Whatever on his mind that</i>
<i>he wanna do with that football,</i>

49:28.590 --> 49:30.092
<i>let him take it further.</i>

49:30.175 --> 49:34.513
<i>And God be on his side with us with him.</i>
<i>He gonna make it.</i>

49:35.639 --> 49:37.015
<i>He gonna make it.</i>

49:50.112 --> 49:52.030
Ooh, hell yeah.

49:55.742 --> 49:57.577
[Ollie] <i>Live for the moment.</i>

49:57.661 --> 50:00.747
<i>Never know when you're gonna die,</i>
<i>so, live for the moment.</i>

50:05.585 --> 50:08.630
<i>I really don't love football...</i>

50:08.714 --> 50:10.549
<i>it's just something I can do.</i>

50:11.967 --> 50:14.344
<i>I'm just worried about</i>
<i>the paychecks really.</i>

50:16.805 --> 50:20.308
<i>I plan on trying to make it to the league.</i>

50:20.392 --> 50:22.978
<i>I hope so.</i>
<i>If that doesn't work out...</i>

50:23.061 --> 50:24.354
<i>uh...</i>

50:24.438 --> 50:26.857
<i>I don't have too many plan B's, so...</i>

50:26.940 --> 50:30.902
<i>the first plan gotta happen.</i>
<i>It gotta happen.</i>

